Spring Replay Site (atm @ http://replays.springrts.com/)
--------------------------------------------------------

Website to upload, download, search and comment replays created by games
running on the SpringRTS engine (http://springrts.com).

Runs on Django / Python (https://www.djangoproject.com/).

Development is done using Django 1.4 and Python 2.7, but it will probably run
(with minor modifications?) with Django 1.2 and Python 2.6.
Latest source code can be found here: https://github.com/dansan/spring-replay-site/

The software is licensed as GPLv3, see COPYING.

Needs
* PIL: http://www.pythonware.com/products/pil/ (dev-python/imaging / python-imaging / etc)
* DB-support: dev-python/mysql-python / python-mysqldb / sqlite/postgres/etc
* django_tables2: https://github.com/bradleyayers/django-tables2
* suds: https://fedorahosted.org/suds/ (dev-python/suds / python-suds / etc)
  - I applied https://fedorahosted.org/suds/ticket/359 (1/2 hunks succeeded -> fixed) 
* django-xmlrpc: https://github.com/Fantomas42/django-xmlrpc
* skills/PythonSkills 0.2.0: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/skills | https://github.com/McLeopold/PythonSkills
* python-magic: http://pypi.python.org/pypi/python-magic/
* timezone defs: dev-python/pytz | python-tz
* django-ajax-selects 1.2.5: https://github.com/crucialfelix/django-ajax-selects/
* django-dajaxice & django-dajax: http://www.dajaxproject.com/ (pip/easy_install django-dajaxice ; pip/easy_install django-dajax)
* jQuery UI: http://jqueryui.com/
* flowplayer: http://flowplayer.org/

Copy local_settings_.py to local_settings.py, and overwrite default settings there.
